/10 bg-[#111] p-4","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex h-8 w-8 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[#2563eb]/20 text-sm font-bold text-[#2563eb]","children":4}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-semibold text-white","children":["Multi-client vs. single-entity",":"]}]," ",["$","span",null,{"className":"text-white/70","children":"Firm-focused tools (Botkeeper) have different UX and pricing than single-entity tools (Docyt). Match to your use case."}]]}]]}],["$","div","4",{"className":"flex gap-4 rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-[#111] p-4","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex h-8 w-8 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[#2563eb]/20 text-sm font-bold text-[#2563eb]","children":5}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-semibold text-white","children":["Pricing model",":"]}]," ",["$","span",null,{"className":"text-white/70","children":"Transaction-based pricing can be expensive for high-volume clients. Flat-fee models are more predictable. Calculate your cost at your current and expected future volume."}]]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-12","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"mb-6 text-2xl font-bold text-white","children":"Frequently Asked Questions"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4","children":[["$","details","0",{"className":"group rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-[#111]","children":[["$","summary",null,{"className":"flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between p-5 text-left font-medium text-white hover:text-[#2563eb]","children":["How accurate is AI bookkeeping really?",["$","svg",null,{"className":"h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 text-white/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180","fill":"none","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","stroke":"currentColor","children":["$","path",null,{"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","strokeWidth":2,"d":"M19 9l-7 7-7-7"}]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"border-t border-white/10 px-5 pb-5 pt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-white/70","children":"After a 30-90 day learning period, leading platforms achieve 85-95% accuracy on transaction categorization for most business types. High-variance businesses (restaurants, construction) see lower accuracy than predictable businesses (SaaS, professional services). Accuracy improves significantly when the AI learns your specific chart of accounts and vendor patterns."}]]}],["$","details","1",{"className":"group rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-[#111]","children":[["$","summary",null,{"className":"flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between p-5 text-left font-medium text-white hover:text-[#2563eb]","children":["Can AI bookkeeping completely replace a bookkeeper?",["$","svg",null,{"className":"h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 text-white/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180","fill":"none","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","stroke":"currentColor","children":["$","path",null,{"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","strokeWidth":2,"d":"M19 9l-7 7-7-7"}]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"border-t border-white/10 px-5 pb-5 pt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-white/70","children":"For straightforward businesses with predictable transactions, AI can handle 80-90% of bookkeeping tasks. However, judgment calls — complex accruals, intercompany transactions, anomaly investigation — still require human expertise. Most firms use AI to eliminate routine work and redeploy their bookkeepers to higher-value review and advisory work."}]]}],["$","details","2",{"className":"group rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-[#111]","children":[["$","summary",null,{"className":"flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between p-5 text-left font-medium text-white hover:text-[#2563eb]","children":["What's the ROI on AI bookkeeping software?",["$","svg",null,{"className":"h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 text-white/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180","fill":"none","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","stroke":"currentColor","children":["$","path",null,{"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","strokeWidth":2,"d":"M19 9l-7 7-7-7"}]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"border-t border-white/10 px-5 pb-5 pt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-white/70","children":"A typical bookkeeper charges $25-60/hour. Botkeeper's platform at $69/month per entity replaces 10-15 hours of monthly bookkeeping work per client. At 15 clients, that's 150-225 hours saved — significant ROI even at the lower end of bookkeeper rates. Factor in the quality consistency AI provides versus human fatigue."}]]}],["$","details","3",{"className":"group rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-[#111]","children":[["$","summary",null,{"className":"flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between p-5 text-left font-medium text-white hover:text-[#2563eb]","children":["How long does it take AI bookkeeping to learn my business?",["$","svg",null,{"className":"h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 text-white/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180","fill":"none","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","stroke":"currentColor","children":["$","path",null,{"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","strokeWidth":2,"d":"M19 9l-7 7-7-7"}]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"border-t border-white/10 px-5 pb-5 pt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-white/70","children":"Most platforms need 2-4 weeks of transactions to establish accurate patterns for your specific vendors and categories. During this period, accuracy may be 70-80%. After 90 days of corrections and feedback, most businesses see 90%+ accuracy. Complex businesses with irregular transactions take longer."}]]}],["$","details","4",{"className":"group rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-[#111]","children":[["$","summary",null,{"className":"flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between p-5 text-left font-medium text-white hover:text-[#2563eb]","children":["Is AI bookkeeping secure?",["$","svg",null,{"className":"h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 text-white/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180","fill":"none","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","